In CrPC chapter:2 and section:6 
 Title: Classes of Criminal Courts 
 Description: Besides the High Courts and the Courts constituted under any law, other than this Code, there shall be, in every State, the following classes of Criminal Courts, namely;

		Courts of Session;
		Judicial Magistrate of the first class and, in any Metropolitan area, Metropolitan Magistrate;
		Judicial Magistrate of the second class; and
		Executive Magistrates.
